{
  "version": "0.9.14.1",
  "build": "2026.07.10",
  "release_date": "2026-07-10",
  "changelog": [
    "feat+fix: v0.9.14.1 — Features, fixes, security and a new sponsor since 0.9.14. FEATURES: the ESXi→PVE migration wizard gains a per-disk QEMU aio-mode selector (threads / native / io_uring) for the migrated target disk (#598 ajoergensen). Maintenance Mode now runs a non-blocking pre-flight RAM check and warns you before evacuating a node would push the remaining nodes past ~90% memory (#611 cybrwerk). The Client Portal gains self-service guest teardown — quota-bound portal users can now destroy their own CTs/VMs, not just create them, behind an opt-in hoster flag with a type-the-name confirm and full audit trail (#556). FIXES: the VM-creation wizard's OVMF quick-templates no longer fail with 'efidisk0=:1' when the EFI storage field is left blank (#607 cybrwerk); behind a reverse proxy the container no longer spams TLS-handshake noise into the logs, and PEGAPROX_BEHIND_PROXY now also routes the console WebSockets through the proxy without needing the Settings toggle (#614 wwwlde). SECURITY: dependency floors raised to clear Aikido findings — cryptography 49 + fido2 2.2.1, pillow 12.3, setuptools 83, requests 2.34 (all as >= floors so future patch bumps roll in cleanly); the remaining request-controlled Site-Recovery log lines are sanitised (CWE-117). SPONSORS: welcome Occentus Network (occentus.net) as a Platinum sponsor. 💚"
  ],
